caption: At the first moment  you arrive in this restaurant  they give you a nice feeling. Very comfortable hosts, it is a friendly restaurant to  pass time with your friends or with your date. delicious  food, experienced  chef de cuisine, reasonable  price and excellent  service. Highly recommended.
Great food and reasonsble prices
Found this gem in Brooklyn. Burgers are amazing . Love this small cozy place! Highly recommended.
Best burger! Price is reasonable. Friendly staff. Will definitely come back.
That chicken sandwich is goooooood
Food was so delicious. The burger and fries were amazing. The thai iced tea was also bomb
Walked in here randomly.... burger was delightful.
Sticky wings were lights out, Hushpuppies had great flavor
The burgers are delicious! Also definitely recommend the strawberry basil lemonade - super refreshing!
buttermilk chicken  is so good

We met with friends at this restaurant for a meeting. my friend recommended this place.  Well, it was a winning. the staff were so friendly and we felt excellent. The meal was yummy. We loved this place very much and we will definitely return to this restaurant. Recommended.

I really wonder why this place has high ratings! The entire order was cold up on pickup! Fries mushy, soggy up on pickup! As if they used someone else’s order since we picked up 15 min after ordering it! I will not go back, nothing Gnarly about this place! Specially when you spend 44$ in 2 burgers n 1 fries! Burgers don’t even taste good...44$ for this? Really? And you wonder if you can keep the customers when you cannot even give warm food

A gem of a find for a quick bite in Park Slope. It’s small (only three 2 tops) but they take cards, the service was quick, and the food was delicious. If you’re hungry but don’t want a full service restaurant this place is perfect.
Awesome beef hamburger with fries👍👍👍 Everything is good!!
Good burgers with good fries and wings. Highly recommended
OMG.  I definitely love this place, the sink fries is so satisfied!! The burger is really juicy too. Mighty wing also amazed me!! Everything is DELICIOUS!!!! Definitely a big “GO BACK” place!!
Place is unprofessional, they lie about their pickup times and are always very late with the orders.  If ordering from them expect a nice wait for burgers and fries.
Cozy place, good and fresh food. You can tell they wait for the order to be place to start preparing the food.
This is one of my go-to spots when a friend visits me and wants to eat a burger
I love this place!! When I'm in town, I make sure to stop here for lunch. The burgers are sooo tasty and juicy
They're cooked fresh, and the bread are so soft. Glad to have tater tots though! Super hot when they come out
Great Place Awesome Food!!!!
Surprisingly good. Hard to find, found it it by mistake and I will definitely go back. It is a very small location, so big parties will not fit.

The first thing I noticed coming in was a sort of homey feeling and ambiance aided by the rough wood features and abundance of plants in the space. The selection on the menu was fine including a few simple snacks. The prices were on par with any other nice burger joint. Their classic burger is beyond delicious. It is juicy and meaty. It is totally worth the trip from Manhattan to Brooklyn.
chicken sandwich is bomb
Best chicken sandwich! I used to be a fry cook and this is perfection

Quick, casual, cheap, and really delicious. I tried the grateful dead burger, the fried chicken sandwich, and fries. I thought everything tasted great. Really happy to have found this spot. Will be back.

Best neighborhood burger place to go. The place is small but very cozy and warm. The grateful dead burger was the BEST burger I ever have. It's so tasty and delicious, also, looks extremely satisfying to me!!! The sink fries is like the heaven...I got everything I like in a large bowl...and the strawberry milkshake...also, the best milkshake I ever had, just couldn't describe how much I love it!!! Definitely will come back with my friends!
Burger was on the small side and average taste. It wasn't as juicy as I thought. Presentation was very nice
This is the burger you crave.
The burgers are rich and delicious! Highly recommend!
Workers are nice and the attire is also amazing. The chicken sandwich was one of the best i have ever have
I love classic burger, it is totally worth the hype
Great little spot for a quick bite and the cashier Ruby is so sweet!
Wings are awesome With the runny egg burger and runny egg fries
Macaroni poppers are too big, and not too much flavor
Awesome. Purely awesome!

First time here with my lady and it was good. A little small and had to wait a little but it was worth it. The classic burger was on point and the strawberry basil lemonade was heavenly it. A great experience 🙂👍🏿
Great food, and excellent service, recommend the sweet potato fries and the burger with a runny egg 😁

Gnarly’s hamburger was the best hamburger I ate in NYC! Adding egg to hamburger is such a good idea 💡. This is a veeery small place but cosy and warm. It is quite messy to eat that hamburger but the waiter kindly said “oh feel free to eat with your hands and in a messy way, we give you wet towel and a lot of napkins” and yes she did 👌🏻 She also gave tap water 💧 . But it’s not the kindness of the waiter, it’s the A-mazing taste of the hamburger 👌🏻👌🏻👌🏻👌🏻💫💫💫💫
Great food, attentive employees
Great little spot! Cool vibes and a delicious thick burger.
Great quality burgers from a small little shop. Definitely recommend getting a runny egg on their burgers.
Came upon this place strolling by... charming! Just had a slushy but will try the food soon..
just a delicious grateful dead burger
I really enjoy the style of this place and the food!

Great humble spot for burgers fries and corn dogs! There's small in door seating or your can grab and go. Burgers are nice big and filling with some flavorful selections. I was surprised by the extras like the corn dog and meatballs. A nice surprise wild card. Great for a quick bite or just sit in and pig out.
Great small place with a Tardis door and amazing sandwiches.  Love this place.  Try the buttermilk chicken sandwich, you won't be disappointed.
Fried chicken sandwich and fries were cold and tasted old. This place use to have the chicken do fresh and hot it was breaking apart. Fell off

i ordered delivery through postmates not too long ago  my order arrived cold my chicken (which was undercooked) sandwich was deconstructed (and not listed as such upon ordering) and the jalapeño poppers were literally just fried mac and cheese balls with some jalapeños insultingly thrown into the container  nice job to whoever did that, I'll tell everyone I know about this experience
Really good services and great burger and fries 👌👍👍👍
Good eats!
Good food, fast service, welcoming staff.

The food is incredible and the staff is super nice. I was very fortunate because I came on a random Sat afternoon so it wasn’t packed because there is only about 6-8 chairs so I wish it was a little bigger.
great service, unmatched food. well worth the hipes

This place has had several installations but Gnarly appesrs to have more than sticking power. It may have staying power. The place is small and menu it limited but.....the food is very delicious. The atmosphere seems like one of light hearted genuine fun.
I had the greatfuldead burger it was a masterpiece .it is pricey but the burger was wonderful thanks
Fast, nice, and great food.
While the food was decent...waiting 1.5 hrs for soup and grilled cheese (that had hardly any cheese on it) to be delivered...is just ludicrous. I'd suggest just eating in.
Great food, not many seats available.
Love the burger!

This is a solid burger spot, extremely affordable price at a fraction. Their menu was named after the popular rock band, i think it is super cool. You can't miss this spot if you are in the area. This is a hole in a wall spot, so look for the tardis door. YES, i meant "Doctor Who"'s tardis door at the entrance. I got "The Beatle's" burger, it extremely juicy and mouthful of flavor that expose inside your mouth when you bite it.
The wings were juicy, crispy and sauced to perfection and the fries were well seasoned and crispy.
perfectly crispy fried mighty wings, their bacon gnarly burger is also amazing Great place we love the food  drinks and service are the best.
Brownstone Brooklyn Dining at its best!
The rolling stone wings are the best !
The Portobello burger is out of this world and so are the delicious slushies and the Japanese soft serve ice cream. Definitely a spot to visit with its eclectic ambiance

Great burger in cool little spot... could be 5 stars but: fries came out almost 10 minutes before the burger which means you either eat them first or cold... and milkshake needed to be thicker. Will certainly return.
The worst union rings in my life.
One of the best burgers I’ve ever had. Prices are fair and staff is friendly. Definitely would go again.
LOVE this place!!! Highly recommended. Burgers and brisket sandwich are amazing

Meh, the Buttermilk Fried Chicken burger was meh. Overpriced! A seamless order for a Classic Burger and Buttermilk Fried chicken burger was over $30 because of an obsurd $4 delivery fee! Not worth the price. Gnarly Eats: The name is self explanatory!

I stopped in for a milkshake with my kids and waited 15 minutes while they proceeded to make food for takeout.  They gave no indication that it would be a long wait.  When I asked how much longer they anticipated they became very agitated with me and ignored me.  Eventually told me it would be five minutes.  I came back 10 minutes later and they told me they had forgotten.  I at least got my money back.

Awesome neighborhood spot! Pretty good sized space in a small restaurant, with a two table outdoor seating area. The host there the night I went was great! She was really nice and had helpful recommendations. They have a pretty good burger selection, which is always exciting! Prices are totally reasonable and they have lunch special deals. Definitely will be back again and again, especially want to order one of those corn dogs! Make sure you grab some softserve to go !
The burgers were amazing.
I like this place because of it small menu of choice sandwiches and sides.
Burgers are great including the Gnarly Burger & Chicken Burger. Usually great service by phone and good food, albeit a bit on the unhealthy side!
Gave me gnarly gas and a gnarly stomach ache, worst business lunch ever.

I love the atmosphere, the server that was there back then was the best! The mushroom burger and the fries w/ the spicy mayo were very good. The regular burger was just Ok. Lunch special is a great deal! Will be back

Such a fun find! Chicken wings are top notch and so are their onion rings.  Friendly staff and fun atmosphere! We recommend eating in-house, by the time you bring take out food home the fried goodness can become a little soggy and greasy. Hands down the best , burgers, dogs, wings. Definitely my favorite. The staff is great!!! Food was amazing! Will be back and def recommending to my friends and fellow yelpers.

You can't go wrong with this hidden gem on south slope. Love the way how they prepared buttermilk fried chicken burger and recently had their pulled pork sliders. They are amazing with lots of flavors with soft brioche bun. This is a MUST try place.

There are a lot of little burger stops popping up everywhere and to tell u the truth it's overwhelming and most of them seem over rated and that's why it was so refreshing to come across Gnarly Eat's Burger. This is the special little gems burger spot. They have a huge variety of different burgers and they focused on quality and small menu.  Burgers aren't hard to make but to make an amazing burger is hard. They also have hit mighty wings that are great, actually the best that i ever had.  The burgers themselves are juicy and never over cooked. i meant the burger juice literally pop out of your mouth while you bite it down. They totally standout from so many competitors in the area. I suggest to stop in if you are in the area. I have not been disappointed yet and neither will you. Highly recommended.  All said and done it's just excellent stop in and taste.
Good burgers!

So yes, I keep coming back here and I keep giving gnarly eats 5 stars because each and every time I go, I NEVER want to leave. The food, the atmosphere, the staff, the drinks....everything is so outstanding!  On my most recent endeavor, I brought a friend who was visiting from LA (so he obviously had high food standards)...but I knew gnarly eats would live up to those. Long story short, he ate his face off and absolutely LOVED every second of it.  We came on a Saturday night and surprisingly got seated immediately this is generally rare for a weekend at gnarly eats because it's always so packed). I had to let him try their famous buttermilk fried chicken burger.....that sauces and juiciness of the chicken is oh so good.

This was the first restaurant I came to when I got to park slope. My girlfriend made recommendation for this place a few days in advance (highly recommended). I've never seen this kind of service.  The waiter was quick, attentive, and really nice! This was 5 star service.  We ordered the buttermilk fried chicken burger, gnarly burger, kitchen sink fries, prickly pear lemonade, and mac'n cheese poppers.  The portions were huge so we shared everything. Food was amazing. Just cant say that enough.  I will definitely be visiting soon.

Food & drinks are fantastic; a bit pricey. They don't skimp on portion size or quality. You order delivery, pick-up, sit in the cozy bar, or at a sidewalk table in the summer. Family friendly, but better for groups of 2-4 people. Not good for large groups. They accept credit and debit cards and of course cash. Not wheelchair accessible. No parking lot or structure.
Dude, this food is good

This place is legit . I've been on the lookout for a good burger option for a minute, their burger it's great enough to keep me coming back for more . Furthermore , I had a bite of their buttermilk fried chicken burger it is to die for .  Lastly ,the fries and mac'n cheese poppers was amazing. Everything was spectacular and service was great so less than 5 stars wouldn't be fair
Place is disgusting ,Chicken sandwich was horrible, Over priced , Sandwiches taste like frozen food . If there was Zero star i would give it Zero Dont waste your money going here .
Great burgers.  Needs more space
This is a tiny place but the food is just amazing and the staff is nice. Prices are also fair.
Amazing burgers! Highly recommended place to eat.
Great food.  Near work, eat there like twice a week.
Try the sweet potato fries and any burger, you won't be disappointed.
This is a tiny little burger bar in Park Slope. The ingredients are fresh, the service is great too.
Went on a Wednesday evening, ordered Red Hot Chili Pepper, sweet potato fries, prickly pear lemonade, and Thai iced tea. Food was delicious and service was excellent.
Loved the food and their basil lemonade is amazing!!!
Classic + Grateful Dead. Not the best burgers, but the service was excellent and the prices are very reasonable
I've live in park slope for 6 years and I can't believe I waited so long to come here. Pleasantly surprised. Staff is super nice too!

Delicious, and we had so much fun with the owner's sister! Sat at the bar telling stories, eating the most incredible Kitchen Sink Fries (seriously try them, you can ask them to leave off the egg if you're skeptical!) When I come back to Brooklyn, will finely come again!
Amazing food. Especially the burger!
The Doctor Who tardis door caught my attention, boy was I happy. The food is really, really good.

Delicious fried chicken sandwich. A simple and straightforward menu with creative burger combinations and tasty side offerings. Small space with limited seating, but a cozy atmosphere. I will definitely be going back.

I'll try not to gush but I love this little place. Family operation - they put a lot of care into their orders and the food is awesome. I'd suggest eating in or picking it up yourself as delivery can be a bit slow and you want to eat it fresh!

A great addition to the neighborhood.  Went for the first time today and had the classic burger while my husband had the chicken sandwich and we shared a side of fries.  Everything was cooked perfectly and very tasty. I loved the addition of red cabbage to give the burger some crunch. The chicken sandwich was quite spicy so be warned!  The place is small but welcoming. We chatted with the owner briefly and he was very friendly.  Looking forward to trying their rolled ice cream when the weather is warmer.
I work for ubereats n I don't really eat frm to many restaurants but this spot is worth it , from the wings to the butter milk chicken ,
Buttermilk fried chicken sandwich is phenomenal!

Gnarly Eats has very tasty food. The burgers are very savory and delicious. The wait can be long during lunch/rush hours but I find it worth it. Can't pass up trying this place. Server Lisa made the experience great, very friendly and professional.
I like this place because of it small menu of choice sandwiches and sides. The space is small, but offers a few stools for casual dining on narrow counters.
Probably one of the best burgers I've had in a long time, loved the decor!
New neighborhood joint. Enthusiastic owner. Great Asian-inspired chicken wings and chicken sandwich. Reasonably priced. I hope it sticks around.
Great place very friendly staff, and food is worth the trip. Definitely will be a regular, when ever on the area.
Best burger ever!!!
